  <!-- images -->
  to add an image into the page you need to use an <img> element This is an empty element, which means no closing tag needed. 
  it must carry the following two attributes src and alt 
  
  src tells browser where to find the image file. this will be a relative url pointing to 
  the image in the site
  
  alt provides a text description of the image which describes the image if you cannot see it
  
  also title attribute with the element to provide additional information about the image often used as alt text
  
  height this specifies the height of the images in pixels
  width this specifies the width of the image in pixels
  
  align attribute was commonly used to indicate how the other parts of a page should flow around an image
  top aligns the first line of the surrounding text with the top of the image
  middle aligns the first line 
  bottom align the first line
  
  Image dimension
  
